o our understanding of contemporary politics in Southeast Asia, and to the study of conflict, peace and security, by highlighting the hidden social dynamics and everyday practices of political violence, ethnic conflict, rebel governance and borderland politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aInsurgencyzBurmazKachin State. 0aInsurgencyzBurmazKaren State. 0aKachin (Asian people)zBurmaxPolitics and government. 0aKaren (Southeast Asian people)zBurmaxPolitics and government. 0aPolitical violencezBurmazKachin State. 0aPolitical violencezBurmazKaren State. 4aAsian Studies. 4aInternational Studies. 4aPolitical Science & Political History.  aPolitical Violence, Non-State Armed Groups, Ethnic Conflict, Southeast Asia, Myanmar, Conflict/War Studies, Asian Studies, Security Studies, International Political Sociology, Borderland Studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065198008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGz978311061013008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2019z9783110606485oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150174010740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501740107423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501740107/original  a978-3-11-061013-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Economics, Law & Social Sciences 2019 ENGb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065198-0  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBAC